## Key Code — The Leak

### Primary leak: `subagent-runner.ts`, lines ~418-422

The `turn_end` event handler creates substep labels by concatenating raw `tr.toolName` + `tr.toolCallId`:

```typescript
// Turn end — capture tool results for tracking
if (event.type === "turn_end") {
    const results = (event as any).toolResults;
    if (Array.isArray(results)) {
        for (const tr of results) {
            if (tr.toolName !== "planSteps" && tr.toolName !== "advanceStep" && tr.toolName !== "reportFinding") {
                const substepLabel = `${tr.toolName} ${tr.toolCallId?.slice(0, 8) ?? ""}`;
                //                                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
                // Produces: "read call_00", "grep call_01", "bash call_02"
                feed = addSubstep(feed, substepLabel);
```

This leaks raw identifiers like:
- `read call_00`
- `grep call_01`
- `bash call_02`
- `find call_03`

### Parallel correct code: `subagent-runner.ts`, lines ~306-310

The `tool_execution_start` handler already creates proper human-readable labels using `toolCallToSubstep()`:

```typescript
// Tool execution started
if (event.type === "tool_execution_start") {
    ...
    const substepLabel = toolCallToSubstep(event.toolName, event.args);
    // Produces: "Reading src/auth.ts", "Searching: pattern", etc.
    feed = addSubstep(feed, substepLabel);
```

### `toolCallToSubstep()` in `activity-feed.ts` (lines ~188-243)

This function correctly maps tool names to human-readable labels:

| Tool Name | Produces |
|-----------|----------|
| `read` | `Reading <path>` |
| `grep` | `Searching: <pattern>` |
| `bash` | `bash: <first word> <rest>` |
| `edit` | `Editing <path>` |
| `write` | `Writing <path>` |
| `default` | `Calling <toolName>...` |

